The project focuses on the integration of Virtual Reality (VR) into medical education, specifically in the field of surgery. Utilizing Unity software, the team has developed VR surgical simulations to enhance the learning experience for aspiring surgeons. The project addresses the limitations of traditional surgical education by providing a risk-free environment for repeated practice, immediate feedback, and skill refinement. The VR environment allows students to immerse themselves in a virtual operating room, interact with anatomical structures realistically, and practice surgical procedures without real-world consequences. The project incorporates a comprehensive approach to VR development in Unity, covering aspects such as learning the basics of Unity, choosing a VR platform, understanding C# programming, exploring Unity's XR Toolkit, creating VR projects, designing VR environments with 3D models, implementing basic VR movements, and setting up Oculus VR integration. 

The Oculus Rift is selected as the hardware for VR simulations, providing a high-quality VR experience with features such as inside-out tracking, Oculus Touch controllers, and a comfortable design. The project emphasizes the importance of hardware compatibility, scene setup, and script development in Unity for successful VR implementation. VR training proves to be a valuable tool in preparing individuals for real-life surgeries, reducing surgery time, minimizing mistakes, and instilling confidence in surgical abilities. The project highlights the transformative impact of VR on surgical education, emphasizing its role in shaping highly skilled and confident surgeons. The outcome of the project demonstrates that VR-trained individuals exhibit enhanced surgical skills. 
